<section sectnbr = "5B">
<servcat sctnbr = "05" scnbr = "02">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENBP70A5206027" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "03" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "1">
<title>
Gear Shift Shaft and Fork Inspection
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206010">Manual Transaxle Unit Dismounting and Remounting</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206015">Manual Transaxle Assembly Disassembly and Reassembly</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Using feeler gauge, check clearance between fork (1) and sleeve (2) and replace those parts if it exceeds limit.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
For correct judgement of part replacement, carefully inspect contact portion of fork and sleeve.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<spec>
<title>
Clearance “a” between fork and sleeve
</title>
<ptxt>
Standard: 0.05 – 0.35 mm (0.002 – 0.013 in.) (Low speed)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Limit: 0.4 mm (0.016 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Standard: 0.05 – 0.35 mm (0.002 – 0.013 in.) (High speed)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Limit: 0.4 mm (0.016 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Standard: 0.05 – 0.35 mm (0.002 – 0.013 in.) (5th &#38; 6th gear)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Limit: 0.4 mm (0.016 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Standard: 0.05 – 0.25 mm (0.002 – 0.010 in.) (Reverse gear)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Limit: 0.4 mm (0.016 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520068.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "68.442mm" ver = "01" gw = "121" gh = "177"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Insert each gear shift shaft into case and check that it moves smoothly. If it does not, correct it using oilstone, reamer or the like.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
